new tears spell is nice and shiney and new, and I got to use aoe on a raid last night... and my hopes are somewhat renewed. So I intend to redouble my efforts and try again.<br><br>Now it's a question of who to look for, and where to fight.<br><br>Naturally there will be at least one wizard =)<br>I can also count on my girlfriend - she's a paladin (51).<br><br>I'm thinking another tank and a cleric would make a nice solid tears group.<br><br>Another option I've been thinking of is tank+cleric+wizard+mage.<br>The tank pulls 2 mobs, mage sics pet on one and tank taunts the other.<br>This seems like an awesome option to me, since the mage can offer both tanking and rain - but will the pet have enough taunt to keep aggro? I'm not sure.<br><br>In either situation, I imagine an enchanter or bard would make an awesome 5th player... and I would probably fill out the last slot with another wizard, mage or rogue... but I'm not looking for a full group yet. I'm looking for the -minimum- set of players required to make this happen.<br><br>For location, I was thinking about chardok. It's new to me (only been there once) and fun to explore... and the chodikai sniffers seem to be on proximity aggro, which is a bonus.<br><br>Any further ideas for group composition or location? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/8/02 10:52:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pillar/Tears group composition</span><hr size=1> I don't know what levels you're thinking, but...<br><br>I've spent most of the last week (since Monday 2/4) in ToFS with guildies.  We've gotten 4 student homework drops in that time, which is great. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Groups have been:<br>1 lvl 36-38 troll war. pulling/ tanking<br>1 lvl 36-38 druid<br>1 lvl 36-38 wizzy (me)<br>either: 1 lvl 46 mage, or 1 lvl 38-40 wizzy<br>one time we had a 35 cleric and a 36 mage<br><br>On the 2nd floor we'd pull 4-8 mobs at once, sic all available pets on the ones that didn't stick to the tank, wait 2 seconds for aggro buildup, then unleash with whatever we had (no rains).  Wizzies = Thunderclap and Cast Force, with the high-level mage he'd use his 180 pt PB spell, and we'd drop the whole train in around 30 seconds every time.  No stuns, and with skins / symbols the casters would take a MAX of 1 bub dmg, for only 20m cast.  So we'd be able to pull off 2 or 3 of these pulls, then med up to full while the mage pets and tank did singles.<br><br>At one point I disbanded to take a cleric friend up to the 3rd floor on a CR (we were getting a 2nd 3rd floor key), gated out and ran back up to 2nd floor to rejoin my group.  They were just starting a pull, and somehow I had gotten group-bugged, so I couldn't be invited.  7 mobs inc, I, solo, got 3 XP messages using Thunderclap and Cast Force, taking 40% damage, using 60mana.<br><br>So, in short - choose your target wisely, and AE groupings of many compositions can work well. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 38th Season<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=2